A nanny, Kemi Odetayo, on Thursday appeared at an Ikeja Magistrates’ Court, for allegedly stealing her employer’s 1,300 dollars, 2,300 Euros and 200 pounds (about N1.499million). Odetayo, 46, who lives at 2, Akanni Dosumu Street, Ilupeju, Lagos, is charged with unlawful entry and stealing, to which she pleaded not guilty. Prosecuting Sergeant Mike Unah said Odetayo committed the offence on May 20 and 25. He alleged that the nanny broke into her employer’s bedroom and stole the money belonging to Mr. Babatunde Sofola. Fashola adjourned hearing till September 11. 